==English==
===Etymology===
"'''[[Too Much Information]]'''," a humorous expression, sometimes known as [[Internet slang]], used in [[North America]] and the [[United Kingdom]] to inform a speaker that he/she is telling or revealing too much about himself/herself or a given topic to the level that the topic becomes gross.  The author of this phrase is unknown, but is a suspected and widely supported idea that it began in the Northwest, United States.

===Noun===
'''TMI'''
# Information of a highly personal nature that may be embarrassing for the receipient.
#: ''She started to talk about her date last night, but I thought it was TMI.''